        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic progressive myoclonic epilepsy characterized by childhood onset of progressive dysarthria myoclonus ataxia seizures and cognitive decline. The disease takes a protracted course with patients surviving into adulthood developing signs and symptoms like psychosis with outbursts of prolonged agitation and screaming spasticity and hyperreflexia confusion mutism and incontinence. There are no visual disturbances. Muscle biopsy shows numerous periodic acid-Schiff-positive inclusions so-called Lafora bodies."
        },
